Project Overview
This project was completed as part of Week 3 of my Data Analytics Internship at AnalystLab Africa. The objective was to strengthen my SQL skills by working with two relational datasets: the Sales Data Sample and the Chinook Database using PostgreSQL.
The project involved importing datasets into PostgreSQL, understanding database relationships, cleaning the data, writing SQL queries, performing joins, subqueries, window functions, and answering business-driven analytical questions. The extracted insights were then presented through an interactive Power BI dashboard for effective data storytelling.
Objectives
Import and manage relational datasets in PostgreSQL.
Clean and validate data before analysis.
Perform SQL operations such as SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, HAVING, and aggregate functions.
Apply advanced SQL concepts including JOIN, Subqueries, ROW_NUMBER(), RANK(), and PARTITION BY.
Generate business insights from sales and customer data.
Design an interactive Power BI dashboard to communicate findings.
Key Insights
Sales Data Sample
Total sales exceeded $8.43 million, indicating strong overall business performance.
Classic Cars generated the highest sales revenue, making it the top-performing product line.
Quarter 4 recorded the highest sales, highlighting a significant seasonal increase in customer demand.
The USA contributed the highest revenue among all countries.
Most orders were successfully Shipped, with only a small percentage of orders being cancelled, disputed, or on hold.
Medium-sized deals represented the largest share of total sales.
A few customers contributed a significant portion of total revenue, indicating the importance of key accounts.
Chinook Database
Customer purchases varied across countries, with some regions contributing more revenue than others.
Invoice analysis identified the highest-spending customers.
Music genres and artists showed different levels of popularity based on purchase frequency.
SQL joins provided insights into relationships between customers, invoices, tracks, albums, and artists.
Recommendations
Increase marketing and promotional campaigns during Quarter 4 to maximize seasonal sales opportunities.
Prioritize inventory and product availability for high-performing product lines such as Classic Cars.
Strengthen customer retention strategies for high-value customers through loyalty programs and personalized offers.
Investigate reasons for cancelled and disputed orders to improve customer satisfaction.
Expand marketing efforts in countries with lower sales performance while maintaining strong engagement in top-performing regions.
Continue monitoring sales trends using dashboards to support data-driven business decisions.

This project demonstrates my ability to transform raw relational data into actionable business insights using SQL and Power BI as part of my ongoing learning journey in data analytics through AnalystLab Africa.
